ZH: 这位先生是我公司的老板。
EN: This man is the boss of our company.

ZH: 那位女士是我妈妈的朋友。
EN: That lady is a friend of my mother.

ZH: 请问您是哪位？我不太认识您。
EN: Excuse me, who are you? I don't really know you.

ZH: 我妹妹是班上的第一位学生。
EN: My sister is the top student in her class.

ZH: 你可以坐在这位空椅子上。
EN: You can sit on this empty chair.

ZH: 他是今年举办比赛的主办人之一。
EN: He is one of the organizers of the competition held this year.

ZH: 我在火车站看到一位老人迷路了。
EN: I saw an old man got lost at the train station.

ZH: 这位医生的技术非常好。
EN: The doctor's skills are very good.

ZH: 请问一下，我想找一位英语翻译员。
EN: Excuse me, I would like to find an English interpreter.

ZH: 他是这家公司的创始人之一。
EN: He is one of the founders of this company.

ZH: 昨天我遇见了一位非常有趣的人。
EN: I met a very interesting person yesterday.

ZH: 这位老师一直在鼓励我们努力学习。
EN: This teacher has been encouraging us to study hard.

ZH: 我把那位老人带到医院接受治疗。
EN: I took the old man to the hospital for treatment.

ZH: 我还没有见过那位新同事。
EN: I haven't met the new colleague yet.

ZH: 请问你是哪位公司的负责人？
EN: May I ask which company you are in charge of?

ZH: 坐在前排的那位女士是我的姑姑。
EN: The lady sitting in the front row is my aunt.

ZH: 这位模特的身材完美无缺。
EN: This model has a perfect figure.

ZH: 她是我的一位很亲密的朋友。
EN: She is a very close friend of mine.

ZH: 我的邻居是一位非常慷慨的人。
EN: My neighbor is a very generous person.

ZH: 这位顾客的态度非常恶劣。
EN: The attitude of this customer is very bad.
